  <div class="lesson-card locked" id="lcard-6" data-lesson="6"><div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(6)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-6">06</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Deep Learning Intro</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">Neural networks, layers, backpropagation, CNNs, RNNs, transformers</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-6"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-6">&#8964;</div></div><div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-6"><h3>Neural Networks — The Foundation of Modern AI</h3>
<p>Deep learning is a subset of machine learning using neural networks with many layers. It powers image recognition, speech recognition, language models, recommendation systems, and generative AI. Understanding its fundamentals helps you know when to use it and why it works.</p>
<h3>How Neural Networks Work</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Neurons</strong> — Nodes that receive inputs, apply weights, and pass output through an activation function</li>
<li><strong>Layers</strong> — Input layer, hidden layers, output layer. "Deep" = many hidden layers.</li>
<li><strong>Weights</strong> — Learnable parameters adjusted during training</li>
<li><strong>Activation functions</strong> — ReLU, Sigmoid, Softmax — introduce non-linearity enabling complex pattern learning</li>
<li><strong>Backpropagation</strong> — Algorithm that calculates how much each weight contributed to the error and updates weights to reduce it</li>
<li><strong>Gradient descent</strong> — Optimisation algorithm: iteratively adjust weights in the direction that reduces loss</li>
</ul>
<h3>Key Architectures</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>CNN (Convolutional Neural Network)</strong> — Designed for images. Learns spatial patterns using convolutional filters. Powers image classification, object detection, medical imaging.</li>
<li><strong>RNN (Recurrent Neural Network)</strong> — Designed for sequences. Maintains memory of previous inputs. Used for time series and early NLP.</li>
<li><strong>LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory)</strong> — Improved RNN that handles long-term dependencies better.</li>
<li><strong>Transformer</strong> — The architecture behind modern LLMs (GPT, Claude, Gemini). Uses attention mechanism. Revolutionised NLP and is now expanding to other domains.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Frameworks</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>TensorFlow/Keras</strong> — Google. Production-friendly. Keras is the high-level API.</li>
<li><strong>PyTorch</strong> — Meta. Research favourite. Dynamic computation graph. Dominant in academia.</li>
</ul>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>Backpropagation</strong> — Algorithm that calculates weight gradients to reduce prediction error<br>
<strong>CNN</strong> — Convolutional Neural Network: designed for image and spatial data<br>
<strong>Transformer</strong> — Architecture using attention mechanisms powering modern LLMs<br>
<strong>Gradient descent</strong> — Iterative optimisation algorithm for adjusting model weights
