  <div class="module-header">&#129302; Module 3 &mdash; Advanced Topics (Lessons 9&ndash;10)</div>
  <div class="lesson-card locked" id="lcard-8" data-lesson="8"><div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(8)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-8">08</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Real-World ML Applications</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">NLP, computer vision, recommendation systems, fraud detection</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-8"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-8">&#8964;</div></div><div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-8"><h3>ML Solving Real Problems</h3>
<p>Machine learning is not an academic exercise — it powers products billions of people use every day. Understanding these applications helps you know where to apply ML in your own projects.</p>
<h3>Natural Language Processing (NLP)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Sentiment analysis — Is this review positive or negative?</li>
<li>Text classification — Is this email spam or not spam?</li>
<li>Machine translation — Google Translate, DeepL</li>
<li>Named entity recognition — Extract names, dates, locations from text</li>
<li>Large Language Models — ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini — general-purpose NLP at scale</li>
</ul>
<h3>Computer Vision</h3>
<ul>
<li>Image classification — What is in this image?</li>
<li>Object detection — Where are the objects in this image? (YOLO, Faster R-CNN)</li>
<li>Facial recognition — Used in security, payment verification</li>
<li>Medical imaging — Detecting tumours, diabetic retinopathy, malaria from microscopy</li>
<li>OCR (Optical Character Recognition) — Extracting text from images and documents</li>
</ul>
<h3>Recommendation Systems</h3>
<p>Used by Netflix, Spotify, TikTok, Amazon, YouTube. Two main approaches:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Collaborative filtering</strong> — Recommend based on what similar users liked</li>
<li><strong>Content-based filtering</strong> — Recommend based on features of items the user has liked</li>
</ul>
<h3>Fraud Detection (African Fintech Context)</h3>
<p>Flutterwave, Paystack, and OPay use ML to detect fraudulent transactions in real time. Features: transaction amount, location, time, device fingerprint, user behaviour. The challenge: severe class imbalance (0.1% fraud rate) requires techniques like SMOTE, class weights, and precision-recall optimisation.</p>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>NLP</strong> — Natural Language Processing: ML applied to text and language<br>
<strong>Computer vision</strong> — ML applied to images and video<br>
<strong>Collaborative filtering</strong> — Recommending based on similar users behaviour<br>
<strong>OCR</strong> — Optical Character Recognition: extracting text from images
