lectOption(this,8,5,2,2)">Natural Language Processing at scale — trained on massive text data for general-purpose language tasks</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,5,3,2)">Fraud detection</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-8-5"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-8-6"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q7</span>What technique helps with severe class imbalance in fraud detection?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,6,0,2)">Ignoring the minority class</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,6,1,2)">Collecting more data forever</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,6,2,2)">Techniques like SMOTE class weights and optimising precision-recall rather than accuracy</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,6,3,2)">Using a simpler model</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-8-6"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-8-7"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q8</span>What is content-based filtering in recommendation systems?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,7,0,1)">Filtering inappropriate content</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,7,1,1)">Recommending items based on features of items the user has previously liked</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,7,2,1)">Collaborative user recommendations</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,7,3,1)">A spam filter</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-8-7"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-8-8"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q9</span>What ML application helps detect diabetic retinopathy?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,8,0,2)">NLP</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,8,1,2)">Fraud detection</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,8,2,2)">Computer vision / medical imaging — analysing retinal photographs to detect disease markers</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,8,3,2)">Recommendation systems</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-8-8"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-8-9"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q10</span>What does YOLO detect?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,9,0,1)">Programming errors</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,9,1,1)">Objects in images in real time — YOLO stands for You Only Look Once</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,9,2,1)">You Online Learning Outputs</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,8,9,3,1)">A type of NLP model</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-8-9"></div></div></div><div class="quiz-actions"><span class="quiz-answered-count" id="qcount-8"><span>0</span>/10 answered</span><button class="quiz-submit-btn" id="qsub-8" onclick="submitQuiz(8)" disabled>Submit &#8594;</button></div><div class="quiz-result" id="qres-8" style="display:none"></div></div></div></div>
  <div class="lesson-card locked" id="lcard-9" data-lesson="9"><div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(9)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-9">09</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Ethics in AI and ML</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">Bias, fairness, explainability, responsible AI, GDPR and AI</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-9"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-9">&#8964;</div></div><div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-9"><h3>Why AI Ethics Matters</h3>
<p>AI systems that make decisions about people — loan approvals, hiring decisions, criminal sentencing, medical diagnoses — have significant ethical implications. Biased training data produces biased models. Opaque models make decisions nobody can explain. These are not hypothetical problems — they are occurring today.</p>
<h3>Bias in Machine Learning</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Data bias</strong> — Historical data reflects historical discrimination. A hiring model trained on past hiring decisions learns to replicate past biases.</li>
<li><strong>Sampling bias</strong> — Training data not representative of the actual population the model will serve.</li>
<li><strong>Label bias</strong> — Human annotators bring their own biases when labelling training data.</li>
<li><strong>Algorithmic bias</strong> — The optimisation objective itself may create unfair outcomes for certain groups.</li>
</ul>
<h3>African Context — Representation Gaps</h3>
<p>Most large ML datasets are dominated by Western, English-speaking data. Facial recognition systems trained primarily on lighter-skinned faces perform significantly worse on darker-skinned faces. Speech recognition fails on African accents. Medical diagnostic models trained on Western patient data may perform poorly in African contexts. African ML practitioners must advocate for and create representative datasets.</p>
<h3>Explainability (XAI)</h3>
<p>Can you explain why your model made a specific prediction? Regulators and users increasingly require this. Tools: SHAP values, LIME, Grad-CAM (for images). Simple models like decision trees are inherently interpretable; complex models like neural networks require post-hoc explanation tools.</p>
<h3>Responsible AI Principles</h3>
<ul>
<li>Fairness — Do not discriminate against protected characteristics</li>
<li>Transparency — Be clear when AI is making decisions affecting people</li>
<li>Accountability — Humans remain responsible for AI-driven decisions</li>
<li>Privacy — Minimise data collection. Protect training data privacy.</li>
</ul>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>Algorithmic bias</strong> — Systematic unfairness in model predictions affecting certain groups<br>
<strong>XAI</strong> — Explainable AI: methods to understand and interpret model decisions<br>
<strong>SHAP values</strong> — A technique to explain individual model predictions by feature contribution<br>
<strong>Representation gap</strong> — Underrepresentation of certain groups in training datasets
