is,9,2,0,1)">Making AI faster</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,2,1,1)">The ability to understand and interpret why a model made a specific prediction — critical for trust accountability and regulation</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,2,2,1)">A type of regularisation</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,2,3,1)">Making AI code readable</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-9-2"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-9-3"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q4</span>What is SHAP?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,3,0,1)">A type of neural network</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,3,1,1)">A method to explain individual predictions by quantifying each feature's contribution to the prediction</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,3,2,1)">A regularisation technique</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,3,3,1)">A model evaluation metric</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-9-3"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-9-4"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q5</span>What representation gap problem affects facial recognition in Africa?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,4,0,1)">African faces are more complex</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,4,1,1)">Systems trained primarily on lighter-skinned Western faces perform significantly worse on darker-skinned faces</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,4,2,1)">African devices have worse cameras</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,4,3,1)">Lighting conditions in Africa</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-9-4"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-9-5"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q6</span>What is sampling bias?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,5,0,1)">Statistical sampling error</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,5,1,1)">Training data that is not representative of the actual population the model will be deployed to serve</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,5,2,1)">A type of label error</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,5,3,1)">Random data selection</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-9-5"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-9-6"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q7</span>What does transparency in responsible AI require?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,6,0,1)">Hiding model architecture</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,6,1,1)">Being clear with users when AI is making decisions that affect them</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,6,2,1)">Publishing all training data</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,6,3,1)">Making models faster</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-9-6"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-9-7"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q8</span>What is a decision tree's advantage in ethics-sensitive applications?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,7,0,2)">It is always more accurate</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,7,1,2)">It is faster to train</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,7,2,2)">It is inherently interpretable — you can trace exactly why each prediction was made</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,7,3,2)">It never produces biased outputs</div></div><div class="q-feedback" id="qf-9-7"></div></div><div class="quiz-q" id="q-9-8"><div class="q-text"><span class="q-num">Q9</span>Why should African ML practitioners advocate for representative datasets?</div><div class="q-options"><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,8,0,1)">African datasets are illegal to use</div><div class="q-option" onclick="selectOption(this,9,8,1,1)">Most large