  <div class="lesson-card locked" id="lcard-10" data-lesson="10"><div class="lesson-header" onclick="toggleLesson(10)"><div class="lesson-num" id="lnum-10">10</div><div class="lesson-info"><div class="lesson-title">Getting Started in ML — Career and Resources</div><div class="lesson-subtitle">Learning path tools datasets competitions certifications</div></div><div class="lesson-status" id="lstatus-10"><span class="lock-icon">&#128274;</span></div><div class="lesson-toggle" id="ltoggle-10">&#8964;</div></div><div class="lesson-body" id="lbody-10"><h3>Your ML Learning Path</h3>
<p>Machine learning is a broad and deep field. The key is starting practical, building projects, and deepening theory as you go. Here is a structured path from beginner to practitioner.</p>
<h3>Phase 1: Foundations (Month 1-3)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Python basics (if not already strong)</li>
<li>NumPy and Pandas for data manipulation</li>
<li>Matplotlib for data visualisation</li>
<li>Statistics basics: mean, median, variance, correlation, probability</li>
</ul>
<h3>Phase 2: Traditional ML (Month 3-6)</h3>
<ul>
<li>scikit-learn: master the API across all major algorithms</li>
<li>Kaggle competitions: practice on real datasets</li>
<li>Build 3 projects: regression, classification, clustering</li>
</ul>
<h3>Phase 3: Deep Learning (Month 6-12)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Neural networks fundamentals</li>
<li>TensorFlow/Keras or PyTorch</li>
<li>Specialise: NLP, computer vision, or tabular data</li>
</ul>
<h3>Essential Resources</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Kaggle</strong> — Free datasets, competitions, courses, and community (kaggle.com)</li>
<li><strong>fast.ai</strong> — Top-down practical deep learning course (fast.ai)</li>
<li><strong>Google ML Crash Course</strong> — Free, beginner-friendly (developers.google.com/machine-learning)</li>
<li><strong>Papers with Code</strong> — Latest research with open-source implementations</li>
<li><strong>Hugging Face</strong> — Pre-trained models and NLP tools (huggingface.co)</li>
</ul>
<h3>ML Career Paths</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>ML Engineer</strong> — Build and deploy ML systems</li>
<li><strong>Data Scientist</strong> — Analyse data and build models for business insights</li>
<li><strong>MLOps Engineer</strong> — Infrastructure and operations for production ML</li>
<li><strong>AI Researcher</strong> — Push the boundaries of what is possible</li>
</ul>
<div class="glossary-box"><span class="gls-title">// Glossary</span>
<strong>Kaggle</strong> — Platform for ML competitions datasets and community learning<br>
<strong>Hugging Face</strong> — Repository of pre-trained models especially for NLP<br>
<strong>MLOps Engineer</strong> — Specialist in deploying and maintaining ML systems in production<br>
<strong>Data Scientist</strong> — Professional analysing data and building models for business insights
